    "sigma_space": "scalar (n, l, m) \u2014 14 nodes at n_max=3",
    "P_space": "Dirac (n, kappa, two_mj) \u2014 varies with n_max",
    "group_structure": "On the full Dirac label space, the three Z_2s generate:   sigma_spinor: m_j -> -m_j (time reversal)   P: kappa -> -kappa (accidental degeneracy / parity)   C: chirality flip (Weyl sector swap) sigma_spinor and P commute (act on different quantum numbers). C acts on a separate index (chirality). Together they generate Z_2 x Z_2 x Z_2 on the full Dirac-on-S^3 space. On the scalar graph, only sigma (= sigma_spinor restricted to m) acts."
